casebody.data:
The People, ex rel. The Twenty-Third Street R. R. Co., Respondent, v. Rollin M. Squire, Commissioner of Public Works of, &c., of New York, Appellant. Decided January 4, 1886. Appeal from order directing writ of mandamus to issue. E. Henry Lacombe, counsel of corporation, &c. Osborn E. Blight, for relator.

Before Sedgwick, Ch. J., Van Vorst and Freedman, JJ.

Per Curiam.

Order affirmed, with costs.
